Class RangeStyleHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.gembox.spreadsheet.internal.styles.AbstractStyleHandler
      • com.gembox.spreadsheet.internal.styles.RangeStyleHandler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AlignmentDataFormatHandler, BorderHandler, CellFormatDataFormatHandler, CellFormatDataFormatHolder, FillDataFormatHandler, FontDataFormatHandler, FormatHandler, NumberDataFormatHandler, ProtectionDataFormatHandler, StyleHandler

    public final class RangeStyleHandler
extends AbstractStyleHandler
implements CellFormatDataFormatHolder
    Represents a style handler for CellStyle returned from AbstractRange.getStyle() method.

      • getStyles

        protected CellStyleCollection getStyles()
        Description copied from class: AbstractStyleHandler
        Gets the styles associated with the workbook to which this style handler belongs.

        This member is required because it provides additional services required by format handlers, like importing style (if it is from another workbook), caching, retrieving color scheme, default / empty formatting and default ('Normal') style.

        Specified by:
        getStyles in class AbstractStyleHandler
        Returns:
        The styles associated with the workbook to which this style handler belongs.

      • getCellFormatHolder

        protected CellFormatDataFormatHolder getCellFormatHolder()
        Description copied from class: AbstractStyleHandler
        Gets the cell format holder.

        Cell format holder is usually a parent editor (ExcelColumnRowBase or ExcelCell) of this cell format handler which either stores or inherits cell formatting.

        For example, ExcelCell can either have cell formatting directly in its data, if it is allocated; otherwise it will inherit cell formatting from either ExcelRow or ExcelColumn or default / empty formatting from the associated workbook.

        Specified by:
        getCellFormatHolder in class AbstractStyleHandler
        Returns:
        The cell format holder.

        public void setCellFormatInternal(CellFormatData value)

        Parameters:

        all - If set to false, then direct borders will be set just to outside columns / rows / cells.

      • getBorderUnresolved

        public Optional<SingleBorderData> getBorderUnresolved(IndividualBorder selector)

        Gets the unresolved (direct) single border formatting.

        If range is merged and all outside columns / rows / cells have the same unresolved (direct) single border formatting, then that formatting is returned; otherwise, null is returned.

        If range is not merged or border is not outside, then unresolved (direct) single border formatting is always taken from the first column / row / cell in the selected outside range.

        Overrides:
        getBorderUnresolved in class AbstractStyleHandler
        Parameters:
        selector - The border selector.
        Returns:
        The unresolved (direct) single border formatting.

      • setBorderInternal

        public void setBorderInternal(EnumSet<MultipleBorders> selector,
                              Optional<SingleBorderData> value)

        Sets the resolved border formatting (clears neighbor borders).

        If all borders are selected and value is null direct borders of all columns / rows / cells will be set to null.

        Diagonal borders are set to all columns / rows / cells. Outside borders are set only to outside columns / rows / cells.

        Overrides:
        setBorderInternal in class AbstractStyleHandler
        Parameters:
        selector - The borders selector.
        value - The border formatting.
